<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7855&amp;p=79667#p79667"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[How should track order be determined?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7855&amp;p=79667#p79667"><![CDATA[
How should track order be determined for a game?<br />There are many possible ways of ordering tracks.  One way is to leave the track numbers alone, but sometimes sound effects are interleaved with the music tracks.<br />Another way is to take the earliest possible time a given track could play.  But then you end up with Jingles intermixed with the rest of the tracks.<br />Another way is to categorize the type of song (map music, battle music, etc), but then you end up with late game songs appearing out of order compared with early game songs.<br /><br />So I really want to know what the best practices are for establishing a track order for a game's soundtrack.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Mon Jun 13, 2011 1:49 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
